						<div class="postbody">8x8 bullets are really useful for maximising sprite bandwidth,and of course VRAM consumption(wich can be a problem for the snes if you're short).<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I think 16x16 bullets just look cooler IMHO, even if they are slightly more flicker prone.</div><br />it's a game design choice, for exemple i dislike Wings of war/gynoug on Md mainly because of his small bullets /sprites .<br />The devs wanted to display the maximum sprites they can be on screen, but they are small and flat, with a very limited number of animation patterns .<br />Personally it's no my cup of tea .</div>

