			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">No, you only get two.  OAM only has one size bit per sprite; it's used to select between the two sizes you specify in OBSEL.<br /><br />I believe you can change the global size setting in OBSEL with HDMA (I tried it, and it looked like it was working), but if you think about how sprites are rendered for a moment you'll realize how easy it is to screw up and get crazy glitching when doing that.  Not only can you end up cutting off large sprites if the new size is smaller, but you can end up with blocks of garbage right below the split if the new size is larger.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

